Definition: refined and tasteful in appearance or behavior or style
Example: elegant handwriting; an elegant dark suit; she was elegant to her fingertips; small churches with elegant white spires; an elegant mathematical solution--simple and precise and lucid
Synonyms: noun, attribute, elegance, INELEGANT, DIGNIFIED, GRACEFUL, REFINED, SOPHISTICATED, TASTEFUL, refined, and, tasteful, in, appearance, or, behavior, style, elegant, handwriting, an, dark, suit, she, was, to, her, fingertips, small, churches, with, white, spires, mathematical, solution--simple, precise, lucid
Category: adj.all
